Headlines.Headline: AOL looks to Cisco for help 8-18-98

#text: America Online (AOL)

turned to Cisco Systems on Tuesday to help unclog its data servers, which handle more than
    18,800 Web hits per second. Cisco (CSCO)

will supply high-speed gigabit routers for AOL's Internet service, which juggle demands of
    more than 730,000 simultaneous users. Financial terms of the deal weren't disclosed.
    Eventually, the routers could help AOL offer so-called quality of service features for
    which customers would pay extra to guarantee immediate delivery of high-priority
    communications, Cisco said. Such features are required for voice or video traffic to be
    delivered without interruption over the Internet. Cisco shares gained 2 3/4 to 100 7/8,
    while AOL rose 6 3/4 to 111 3/16.
